  "doc_id": "21168",
  "text": "Coat hanger. The triangular-shaped apparatus consisted of a horizontal steel wire (diameter: 2 mm, length: 41 cm) flanked at each end by two sidebars (length: 19 cm; inclination: 351 from the horizontal axis). [CITATION_1] The horizontal bar was placed at a 45 cm height from the floor. The mice were placed upsidedown in the middle of the horizontal wire and released only after gripping with all four paws. Latency before falling was recorded. A trial ended when the mice fell or reached the top of the apparatus, from which it was retrieved and the maximal score of 1 min given for latencies before falling. A block of five consecutive trials was applied with a 15-min intertrial interval and a 1-min cut-off period per trial.",
